import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'], label='Wheat Production', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.scatter(data['wheat'], data['wages'], label='Wheat vs Wages')
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.ylabel('Wages')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wheat production and wages?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.hist(data['wheat'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Wheat Production')
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['wheat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wheat production?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    avg_data = data.groupby('year').mean().reset_index()

    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()

    ax1.bar(avg_data['year'], avg_data['wheat'], color='b', alpha=0.5, label='Average Wheat Production')
    ax2.plot(avg_data['year'], avg_data['wages'], color='r', label='Average Wages')

    ax1.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax1.set_ylabel('Average Wheat Production')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Average Wages')
    ax1.set_xticks(avg_data['year'])
    ax1.set_xticklabels(avg_data['year'], rotation=45)

    lines, labels = ax1.get_legend_handles_labels()
    lines2, labels2 = ax2.get_legend_handles_labels()
    ax2.legend(lines + lines2, labels + labels2, loc='upper left')

    plt.title('What is the average wheat production and wages per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
